message.content:
cs.NE, cs.DC, cs.Distributed, cs.AI, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely category as the paper describes a distributed simulator of plastic spiking neural networks and discusses the comparison with another neural simulation tool.
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also likely as the paper focuses on the scalability of the simulator up to 1024 software processes and hardware cores.
- cs.Distributed is another possible category as the paper describes a distributed simulation of a neural network over a set of MPI processes.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper discusses the simulation of a large-scale neural network and its potential applications in cognitive and systems neuroscience.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a less likely category but still possible as the paper discusses the development of the DPSNN simulator in the framework of the EURETILE and CORTICONIC European FET Project and its use in the Human Brain Project.
